# Agentic Digital Marketing Platform — Production Guardrails

## Data access
- NEVER use raw SQL in application code. Use SQLAlchemy ORM, repository pattern, or query builders with parameterized statements only.
- All database queries MUST filter by `tenant_id`. No global queries without tenant scope.
- LangGraph checkpoints and thread IDs MUST be namespaced with `{tenant_id}:` prefix.

## Architecture
- Use dependency injection (FastAPI `Depends`, constructor injection in Python services).
- All public HTTP routes MUST declare OpenAPI metadata (`summary`, `response_model`, `tags`).
- Enforce strict tenant isolation at API middleware, repository, and agent layers.

## Security
- Agents authenticate with proof-of-possession (DPoP/mTLS) tokens — never human OAuth flows for autonomous execution.
- MCP tool schemas MUST be hash-verified before invocation; block on rug-pull drift.
- PII MUST pass through the NER gateway before reaching core LLMs.
- Financial write actions REQUIRE idempotency keys.

## Agent runtime
- Code execution ONLY in Firecracker microVM sandboxes — never standard Docker for agent-generated code.
- On guardrail breach or network timeout: circuit breaker → Safe Mode (read-only).
- Enforce MVG: token budgets, wall-clock limits, behavioral caps, predictive pre-step reservations.

## Marketing & compliance
- Label conversions as `observed` vs `modeled` (Consent Mode v2); never optimize on modeled data alone.
- Generative outputs MUST pass FTC/CMA compliance checks at inference layer.
- Competitive intelligence ingestion MUST run embedding-based IPI anomaly detection.

## Code quality
- Match existing patterns; minimal scope per change.
- Do not auto-format during agent operations if formatters conflict with Review Tab.
